{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/comments/371203699", "html_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/17467#issuecomment-371203699", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/17467", "id": 371203699, "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM3MTIwMzY5OQ==", "user": {"login": "ebrevdo", "id": 1794715, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE3OTQ3MTU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/1794715?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ebrevdo", "html_url": "https://github.com/ebrevdo", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ebrevdo/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ebrevdo/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ebrevdo/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ebrevdo/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ebrevdo/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ebrevdo/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ebrevdo/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ebrevdo/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ebrevdo/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "created_at": "2018-03-07T16:50:26Z", "updated_at": "2018-03-07T16:50:37Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "body_html": "<p>You can sample from a Rayleigh distribution using the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rayleigh_distribution#Generating_random_variates\" rel=\"nofollow\">uniform sampler</a>.  Use <code>tf.random_uniform</code> and then pass it through</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-python\"><pre>x <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> sigma <span class=\"pl-k\">*</span> tf.sqrt(<span class=\"pl-k\">-</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">2</span><span class=\"pl-k\">/</span>np.log(<span class=\"pl-c1\">2</span>) <span class=\"pl-k\">*</span> tf.log(u))</pre></div>\n<p><a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=1137078\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/jvdillon\">@jvdillon</a> we can add this as a distribution pretty easily.</p>", "body_text": "You can sample from a Rayleigh distribution using the uniform sampler.  Use tf.random_uniform and then pass it through\nx = sigma * tf.sqrt(-2/np.log(2) * tf.log(u))\n@jvdillon we can add this as a distribution pretty easily.", "body": "You can sample from a Rayleigh distribution using the [uniform sampler](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rayleigh_distribution#Generating_random_variates).  Use `tf.random_uniform` and then pass it through\r\n\r\n```python\r\nx = sigma * tf.sqrt(-2/np.log(2) * tf.log(u))\r\n```\r\n\r\n@jvdillon we can add this as a distribution pretty easily."}